      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:7:16:11",
      "text": [
        " مَنْ شَرِبَ شَرْبَةً مِنْ خَمْرٍ لَمْ يَقْبَلِ اللَّهُ مِنْهُ صَلَاتَهُ أَرْبَعِينَ يَوْماً ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali, from his father, from Al Nazar Bin Suweyd, from Hisham Bin Salim, from Suleyman Bin Khalid, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘The one who drinks a drink from wine, his Prayer would not be Accepted from him for forty days’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "11. Ali has narrated from his father from al-Nadr ibn Suwayd from Hisham ibn Salim from Sulayman ibn Khalid who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘If one drinks one sip of wine his Salat (prayer) is not accepted for forty days.’” "
        ]
      }
